cluster_relations.rel_desc: Ethical guidelines are presented as a means to ensure that accountability is properly assigned.

qualifiers.OperationalConstraint: in the development and deployment of AI technologies

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Regulations are framed as mechanisms to ensure proper assignment of accountability.

qualifiers.OperationalConstraint: in the development and deployment of AI technologies

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject (such as a guideline or regulation) is designed to foster or ensure proper accountability in the context of AI development and deployment.
args.justification: Both relations describe normative instruments (ethical guidelines, regulations) whose functional purpose is to ensure proper assignment of accountability in AI. A single predicate 'promotes_accountability' captures this directed support/assurance role without overfitting to a specific mechanism.

These relations form a coherent family where governance instruments (guidelines, regulations, frameworks) provide structures or mechanisms that support or secure accountability outcomes in AI systems.

The descriptions emphasize that guidelines and regulations exist to ensure accountability, implying a purposive causal relationship where the subject contributes to bringing about accountability outcomes.
args.remark: Also has a normative/functional flavor, but CAUSALITY best captures that these instruments are mechanisms intended to lead to accountability.
